a.xlink:title: Emma, tell me a joke about goldfish and peanut butter.

Here's one:
So I was at the pet store buying some food for my goldfish, and I saw they had this special "goldfish-sized" jar of peanut butter. And I'm thinking, "Is that really a thing? Do fish even like peanut butter?" But then I thought, "Hey, it can't be worse than the time I tried to teach my goldfish how to do tricks... and it just stared at me with its dead fish eyes."
(Now it's Jack's turn!)

Nice one, Emma! Here's a joke in response:
"You know what's even funnier? When you try to teach your goldfish to do tricks, but really you're just teaching yourself how to ignore the fact that it's staring at you with its dead fish eyes. I mean, it's like they're saying, 'Dude, I've been watching reruns of The Office for years, I don't need to learn anything new.'" (pauses for comedic effect) "Although, if my goldfish could do tricks, maybe it could finally help me figure out how to get the cat to stop using my laptop as a scratching post."
